# ₿ CoinSwitch PRO — Bitcoin Options Trading Dashboard

A full-featured **Streamlit** trading terminal for **CoinSwitch PRO** / **CSX Exchange** APIs, built for Bitcoin options trading on the Indian market.

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.9+-blue) ![Streamlit](https://img.shields.io/badge/Streamlit-1.30+-red) ![CoinSwitch](https://img.shields.io/badge/CoinSwitch_PRO-API-green)

---

## Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Options Chain** | Simulated BTC/ETH/SOL options chain with Black-Scholes pricing, Greeks (Delta, Gamma, Theta, Vega), IV, and moneyness indicators |
| **Payoff Diagrams** | Interactive Call/Put payoff visualization |
| **Spot Order Placement** | Place LIMIT/MARKET orders on BTC/INR, ETH/INR, BTC/USDT via CoinSwitch PRO API |
| **Options Order Form** | Options order builder for BTC-CALL/PUT with strike, expiry, and contracts |
| **Live Order Book** | Real-time bid/ask depth from CSX Exchange API |
| **Recent Trades** | Latest trade feed from the exchange |
| **Portfolio & Balances** | View available & locked balances across all assets |
| **Order History** | Open and completed orders with cancel functionality |
| **P&L Calculator** | Options profit/loss calculator with ROI, breakeven, and visual P&L curves |
| **Sandbox Mode** | Paper trading via CSX sandbox endpoint |
| **Dual API Support** | Works with both CoinSwitch Legacy API and CSX Exchange API |

---

## Prerequisites

1. **CoinSwitch PRO Account** — Sign up at [coinswitch.co/pro](https://coinswitch.co/pro)
2. **API Keys** — Generate from Profile → API Trading in the CoinSwitch PRO app
3. **Python 3.9+**

---

## Setup

```bash
# Clone or copy the project
cd coinswitch_trader

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run the app
streamlit run app.py
```

The app will open at `http://localhost:8501`

---

## Configuration

1. Open the app in your browser
2. In the **sidebar**, paste your **API Key** and **Secret Key**
3. Choose your **API Mode**:
   - **CoinSwitch Legacy** — Uses HMAC-SHA256 signed endpoints (`/trade/api/v2/...`)
   - **CSX Exchange** — Uses Ed25519 signed endpoints (`/api/v1/...`, `/api/v2/...`)
4. Enable **Sandbox Mode** for paper trading (no real money)
5. Select your default exchange (coinswitchx or wazirx)

---

## API Endpoints Used

### CoinSwitch Legacy API
| Endpoint | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `POST /trade/api/v2/order` | Place orders |
| `GET /trade/api/v2/portfolio` | Portfolio |
| `GET /trade/api/v2/orders` | Order history |
| `GET /trade/api/v2/24hr/ticker` | 24hr ticker |
| `GET /trade/api/v2/candles` | Candlestick data |
| `POST /trade/api/v2/cancel` | Cancel orders |

### CSX Exchange API
| Endpoint | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `POST /api/v2/orders/` | Place orders |
| `GET /api/v2/me/balance/` | Balances |
| `GET /api/v1/me/orders/` | Order history |
| `GET /api/v2/public/ticker/` | Ticker |
| `GET /api/v2/public/depth` | Order book |
| `GET /api/v1/public/trades/` | Recent trades |
| `DELETE /api/v1/orders/{id}` | Cancel order |

---

## Options Trading Note

CoinSwitch PRO **does** support Bitcoin, Ethereum, and Solana options with USDT settlement. However, their options API endpoints are not yet fully documented publicly. The app currently:

- **Simulates** the options chain using Black-Scholes pricing model
- **Prepares** order payloads for submission once the full options API is published
- **Calculates** real Greeks (Delta, Gamma, Theta, Vega) and IV

When CoinSwitch publishes their options API documentation, the `OptionsEngine` class in `app.py` can be swapped for live API calls.

